Privacy Policy for .Scroll
This Privacy Policy describes how .Scroll Technologies, Inc. ("we", "us", or ".Scroll") collects, uses, and protects any information that you provide when using the .Scroll mobile application ("app").

Information Collection and Use:
No Data Collection: .Scroll does not collect any personal information, login credentials, or usage data from its users. We respect your privacy and do not track, collect, or store any data that could identify you personally.

Information Sharing:
No Information Sharing: .Scroll does not share any information with third parties as we do not collect any user data.

Data Security:
Secure Environment: While we do not collect any user data, we take reasonable measures to ensure the security of our app and protect against unauthorized access or disclosure.

Children's Privacy:
Compliance with COPPA: .Scroll is intended for general audiences and does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately, and we will take appropriate action to remove such information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy:
Updates: We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated Privacy Policy on our website.

Contact Us:
If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or the .Scroll app, please contact us at:

Email: privacy@scrollapp.com

